{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "18", "S": "20"}}, "news": [{"title": "Concrete plants not green, can\u2019t have them in industrial estates: Goa Inc", "para": "Goa's industrial associations are raising alarms over Ready-Mix Concrete (RMC) plants in estates, citing dust and slurry spills that disrupt clean manufacturing, particularly for pharma and food units. Despite being green-categorized, these plants cause operational issues, prompting fears of relocation. Concerns were voiced at a GIDC meeting regarding indirect entry of RMC units.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/goa-industrial-bodies-oppose-concrete-plants-in-estates-over-pollution-concerns/125213843?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-247728/125213843.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}, {"title": "Maharashtra: Only 25% slum rehabilitation goal met in three years", "para": "Maharashtra's slum rehabilitation program is significantly behind schedule, having completed only 25% of its 1.5 lakh tenement target for 2022-25. This slow pace jeopardizes the larger goal of constructing over 5 lakh houses by 2030. Experts point to cost constraints and suggest slum upgradation as a more viable alternative.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/maharashtras-slum-rehabilitation-effort-falls-short-only-25-completed-in-three-years/125213731?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-122410/125213731.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "East Bengaluru residents decry G+5 buildings on 18-foot road, fear layout will collapse", "para": "Residents of Nanjappa Layout are protesting unauthorized G+5 apartment constructions on an 18-foot road, alleging builders are violating height and safety norms. Despite repeated complaints to the Greater Bengaluru Authority (GBA), no action has been taken, leading to concerns about choked infrastructure and overcrowding.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/residents-protest-against-illegal-g5-constructions-in-east-bengaluru/125213610?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-36856/125213610.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}